summary: This is an FBI communication form (likely a lead sheet or cover memo) dated October 13, 2010, from the Newark/Trenton office to the Miami/Palm Beach office. It concerns the obstruction of justice case against Alfredo Rodriguez and indicates that a lead has been covered following an interview documented in an enclosed FD-302 form.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Named as the subject in the case titled 'ALFREDO RODRIGUEZ OBSTRUCTION OF JUSTICE.' The document is a notification that a lead related to his case has been covered.

events.title: Interview related to Alfredo Rodriguez case
events.description: An interview was conducted, and its details were documented in an enclosed FD-302 form. This led the Trenton office to consider a lead in the case covered.

keyFacts: The document is part of the FBI's investigation into Alfredo Rodriguez for obstruction of justice (Case ID: 72-MM-113327).
An interview was conducted on October 12, 2010, and documented in an FD-302 form.
The Newark/Trenton office is notifying the Miami/Palm Beach office that a lead in the case has been covered.
The document is a routine inter-office communication regarding the status of an investigative lead.
